      {
         "name":"B",
         "description":"Short Answer Questions",
         "questions":[
            {
               "questionNumber":19,
               "text":"How can we help someone with cholera? List any four practices to ensure good health.",
               "type":"short-answer",
               "correctAnswer":"a) Take the patient immediately to the hospital for treatment, Give the person rehydration salts/fuids, Give the patient the Intravenous fluids and electrolyte. b) Daily practices to ensure good health include: i) Brushing our teeth three times in a day and every after a meal. ii) Practicing moderate physical exercises iii) Healthy eating: balanced diet, avoid too much fats/eating at close intervals iv) Vaccination and immunisation practices v) Regular medical check-up in hospitals vi) Sanitation i.e keeping our surroundings clean.",
               "points":10
            },
            {
               "questionNumber":20,
               "text":"Describe the negative impact of monoculture system to the biological diversity in an ecosystem.",
               "type":"short-answer",
               "correctAnswer":"Monoculture crops have no genetic variability because they are not allowed to reproduce naturally.",
               "points":10
            },
            {
               "questionNumber":21,
               "text":"Answer the following in relation to blood. What is blood plasma? Give the role of blood plasma. The ABO blood group system has four blood groups. Name them. Blood groups can be positive (+) or negative (—) according to whether the blood contains or does not contain a particular factor. Name this factor. Suggest a reason why it is important to know a person's blood group. What is the function of platelets in the blood?",
               "type":"short-answer",
               "correctAnswer":"a) Liquid part of blood, b) Plasma transports blood cells, nutrients such as glucose and amino acids; transports antibodies, metabolic waste products... c) ABO blood group system has four blood groups: A, B, AB, O. d) Rhesus factor or Rh factor. e) For proper blood transfusion, to avoid incompatibility of blood/agglutination/ in case of blood transfusion / For Safe organ transplant. f) Platelets are responsible of blood clotting.",
               "points":10
            },
            {
               "questionNumber":22,
               "text":"A man whose blood group is A marries a woman whose blood group B. If one of their children is blood group O: What are the genotypes of their parents? Use a Punnett square to determine the genotype of the other children.",
               "type":"short-answer",
               "correctAnswer":"a) Genotypes of the parents: AO and BO or I4 I° and I°. b) Phenotype of parents: group A x group B, Genotype of parents: I* I9 x I* I9, Gametes: A, O and B, O",
               "points":10
            },
            {
               "questionNumber":23,
               "text":"What do you understand by the term mitosis? Mitosis is essential in all living organisms. Give reasons to support your answer.",
               "type":"short-answer",
               "correctAnswer":"a) Mitosis: is a type of cell division in which a parent cell divides itself into two identical daughter cells which are genetically the same as the parent cell. b) Reasons: It facilitates repair of worn out body tissues, It leads to body building hence growth, It brings about regeneration of parts of organisms e.g. in reptiles, It is responsible of replacement of worn out cells, It provides a basis for asexual reproduction, It maintains genetic stability/the number of chromosomes in the nucleus is retained.",
               "points":10
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "name":"C",
         "description":"Essay/Long Answer Questions",
         "questions":[
            {
               "questionNumber":24,
               "text":"Assume you are performing an experiment to demonstrate osmosis. Enumerate the apparatus and chemicals you may use in your demonstration. Suggest a control that you might use in this activity. State the result(s) of the demonstration. Briefly explain the result(s). Suggest how storing food in salty water prevents the growth of bacteria or fungi on the stored food. Apart from the method described in (e) above, suggest any other way of preventing food spoilage.",
               "type":"essay",
               "correctAnswer":"a) Diagram of osmosis set-up: Two solutions and a membrane, Labels: e.g. water; salt or sugar solution; visking tubing or potato; beaker, b) Control: e.g. Only water in visking tubing and in the beaker; only water around the semi permeable membrane. c) Result: The visking tubing increase in size if it contains a salt or sugar solution. Or water moves from hypotonic solution to hypertonic d) The visking tubing increase in size if it contains a salt or sugar solution. Or water moves from hypotonic solution to hypertonic e) Storing food in salty water prevents the growth of bacteria or fungi on the stored food because the salty water is hypertonic to the bacteria or fungi cells. f) Apart from the method described in (e) above, suggest any other way of preventing food spoilage: Refrigeration, Freezing, Dehydration, Canning, Pickling",
               "points":15
            }
         ]
      }
   ]
